title: A speech made to his Excellency the Lord General Monck, and the Council of State, at Goldsmiths Hall in London, the tenth day of April, 1660. At which time they were entertained by that honourable company. After a song in four parts, at the conclusion of a chorus, enter a sea-captain.
author: Jordan, Thomas, 1612?-1685?
publisher: Printed for H.B. at the Gun in Ivy-lane,
